About this hotel

Set in the Medina, this elegant hostel is a 5-minute walk from lively Jemaa el-Fnaa market square. It's also 2 km from the ornate Bahia Palace and 3 km from the picturesque Majorelle Garden.

Check-in time: 2:00 PM
Check-out time: 10:00 AM

    Natalie Wesbroom4 years ago on Google

    This hostel has good facilities and a lovely sun terrace with superb views. It's in a great location, ticked down an alley off a Souk, which I felt perfectly safe walking to on my own at any time. The breakfast that was included was also really good.
    Wifi not very good though.
    The downside to this hostel was one of the reception staff. I had something taken from my room she put the blame on me straight away because I hadn't used my locker.
    I had locked my room and I believe it was left open by a cleaner as I had noticed this happen a couple of times during my stay, but when I explained this she didn't want to know. I wouldn't be surprised if this had happened before judging by how defensive she was. She also said she didn't care that I would write a review about the security.
    The same receptionist also gave me the wrong time to meet for a tour I booked through the hostel. Luckily I happened to go to reception early, otherwise they would have left without me.

    Rahba Kedima

    Lively Rahba Kedima centers on the souks, a warren of alleys near Rue Semmarine, all packed with small shops selling leather slippers, ceramics, and jewelry. The Muse de la Musique explores local musical culture with instruments, photos, and performances in a restored 16th-century house. Ornate pavilions and pools sit amid lush vegetation in the tranquil Jardin Secret, and hip roof-terrace cafes dot narrow lanes.

    About this hotel

    Set in the Medina, this elegant hostel is a 5-minute walk from lively Jemaa el-Fnaa market square. It's also 2 km from the ornate Bahia Palace and 3 km from the picturesque Majorelle Garden.

    The stylish mixed and female-only dorms provide linens and lockers, and feature bunk beds. Private rooms sleep up to 3 guests. Bathrooms are en suite.

    Continental breakfast is free. There's also a restaurant and a bar. Other amenities include a rooftop terrace, communal lounges, and a spa offering a hammam. A courtyard has a seasonal outdoor pool and a fountain, and coin-operated laundry facilities are on-site.
